{
  "stem": "19550.7",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 223.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "It took about a week because the rails were bombed out.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And probably, there was no coal for the railroad.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And maybe there wasn't even an engineer to drive the railroad.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "It-- we just kept moving, literally a kilometer or two, and then we would halt, and so this 30 kilometers to Tutzing-- T-U-N-I-Z, or zed, I-N-G.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "We were on Lake Starnberg, a rather famous resort area.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And we finally halted at this railroad station.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And we must have been there for two days or so.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "The highway, apparently, was running parallel to the railroad, maybe a few hundred yards away from the rails.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And one fine day, we saw-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] after we heard for the whole day the bombardment and the cannons, we saw, on the one hand, the Germans rushing helter skelter away from there, and these beige tanks with four or five pointed star, white star, coming towards us on the road.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And then one of these tanks sort of peeled off, drove through the grass to the railroad, and some soldiers jumped out.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "We didn't know what kind of soldiers they were, until sort of it became clear that they were Americans.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And we were told we were liberated.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And prior to that, I had made one of my many attempts to escape, and I was shot in the heel.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And I was kind of bloodied.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And some friends of mine who were some fellow prisoners sort of picked me up.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And they took me to a villa that was right next to the railroad station, and deposited me there with two German women, obviously a mother and daughter.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
